  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Statement.}\nA quantum field on a Trawinistic manifold is a section of an appropriate fibre bundle whose dynamics are governed by covariant field equations using the Trawinistic connection.\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nLet $E\\to M$ be a fibre bundle over the Trawinistic manifold $M$.  \nA field configuration is a section:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\phi:M\\to E .\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe dynamics of the field must respect the geometry of $M$, so ordinary derivatives are replaced by Trawinistic covariant derivatives:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\partial_a\\phi\n\\quad\\longrightarrow\\quad\n\\nabla^T_a\\phi .\n\\end{equation}\n\nA generic covariant field equation therefore takes the form:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{F}\n\\left(\n\\phi,\\nabla^T\\phi,g\n\\right)\n=\n0 .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nQuantum fields on a Trawinistic manifold are geometric objects whose evolution is determined by TZP-compatible covariant differential structure.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
